	He traced a finger up and down his cheek bone.  �It�s funny but, the pain - I kind of liked it.  It was my own.  Does that make sense?�
	�It does.� Paul said.
	�Paul, there you are.  I was begining to doubt your presence.  I want you to know that the radishes are fine.  And the carrots.�
	�That's good,� Paul insisted earnestly, �but you know you can�t live there.�
	Jacob nodded.  �It appears not.  I have to - � Jacob shook his head - �How do you get a house?  If I were to knock, and offer a price -�
