	�Ok ok here we are.�  Peter pulled his car up beside one of several shops lining an old neighborhood road - the entrance, the entire length of the store was decorated with large skulls made of plastic, plaster, some as tall as the door.  Chicken wire wrapped over them and held articles bundles of bones, staffs, and plastic weapons, beneath a large hand-painted sign which read in old-style serif - �Flossy McGrew�s�.
	�Jacob!� Peter announced to the skeptical crowd.  �You need to become someone.  Someone different.  We're going to go in here, and turn you into a different person.  Grandma Goth is going to help.�
